  </oversight_info>
  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Dystonia is increasingly being considered as a multi-nodal network disorder involving both
      basal ganglia and cerebellar dysfunction. The aim of this study is to determine if
      &quot;Multi-Target&quot; Thalamic and Pallidal Deep Brain Stimulation improves hemi-dystonia patients
      who are receiving inadequate therapy from GPi DBS.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
